metadata.name: Two-headed wise crow
metadata.description:
I compare Istanbul to this two-headed crow. A wise crow, one side in europe but its real essence and body in asia.

I am an Istanbul photographer. These streets are my studio and my material. Therefore, every single work of mine revolves around and relates to Istanbul. As I walk the streets of this city, I find myself choosing between old and new, beautiful or ugly, love and hate. I take pictures using only my muscle memory and index finger and not fearing my mistakes and accidents, in fact learning from them.
